      "source": [
        "# Taller de IA: NumPy, Matplotlib y Seaborn\n",
        "\n",
        "**Parte I – Ejercicios prácticos:** este notebook contiene todo el código solicitado, listo para ejecutarse en Google Colab."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 1. NumPy – Manipulación de arrays"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "\n",
        "matriz = np.array([\n",
        "    [10, 20, 30],\n",
        "    [40, 50, 60],\n",
        "    [70, 80, 90]\n",
        "])\n",
        "\n",
        "print(matriz)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Actividades: elemento central, segunda fila y tercera columna"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Elemento central\n",
        "print(\"Elemento central:\", matriz[1, 1])\n",
        "\n",
        "# Segunda fila\n",
        "print(\"Segunda fila:\", matriz[1, :])\n",
        "\n",
        "# Tercera columna\n",
        "print(\"Tercera columna:\", matriz[:, 2])"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 2. Operaciones matemáticas"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "datos = np.array([12, 18, 20, 25, 30, 35, 40])\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Promedio:\", np.mean(datos))\n",
        "print(\"Máximo:\", np.max(datos))\n",
        "print(\"Mínimo:\", np.min(datos))\n",
        "print(\"Desviación:\", np.std(datos))"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 3. Generación de datos aleatorios – Distribución normal"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "datos_normales = np.random.normal(\n",
        "    loc=50,    # media\n",
        "    scale=10,  # desviación estándar\n",
        "    size=1000  # cantidad de datos\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.hist(datos_normales, bins=30, color=\"skyblue\", edgecolor=\"black\")\n",
        "plt.title(\"Distribución normal generada (loc=50, scale=10)\")\n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"Valor\")\n",
        "plt.ylabel(\"Frecuencia\")\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 4. Matplotlib – Gráfico de líneas\n",
        "\n",
        "> Concepto a investigar: **accuracy** (precisión del modelo) y **época** (una pasada completa del algoritmo de entrenamiento por todo el conjunto de datos). La explicación completa está en `README.md`."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "epocas = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8]\n",
        "accuracy = [60, 68, 75, 81, 85, 88, 90, 92]\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.plot(epocas, accuracy, marker=\"o\")\n",
        "plt.title(\"Accuracy por época\")\n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"Épocas\")\n",
        "plt.ylabel(\"Accuracy\")\n",
        "plt.grid(True)\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 5. Histograma"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "datos_hist = np.random.normal(70, 15, 1000)\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.hist(datos_hist, bins=30, color=\"salmon\", edgecolor=\"black\")\n",
        "plt.title(\"Histograma de datos (media=70, sd=15)\")\n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"Valor\")\n",
        "plt.ylabel(\"Frecuencia\")\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 6. Gráfico de barras"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "clases = ['Sano', 'Roya', 'Mosaico', 'Mancha']\n",
        "cantidad = [1200, 850, 430, 320]\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.bar(clases, cantidad, color=[\"green\", \"orange\", \"red\", \"brown\"])\n",
        "plt.title(\"Distribución de clases\")\n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"Clase\")\n",
        "plt.ylabel(\"Cantidad de muestras\")\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 7. Seaborn – Mapa de calor (matriz de correlación)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import seaborn as sns\n",
        "\n",
        "datos_df = pd.DataFrame({\n",
        "    'Edad': [20, 25, 30, 35, 40],\n",
        "    'Horas': [2, 4, 6, 8, 10],\n",
        "    'Nota': [60, 70, 80, 90, 100]\n",
        "})\n",
        "\n",
        "correlacion = datos_df.corr()\n",
        "\n",
        "sns.heatmap(correlacion, annot=True, cmap=\"coolwarm\")\n",
        "plt.title(\"Matriz de correlación\")\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 8. Boxplot"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "sns.boxplot(x=datos_df[\"Nota\"])\n",
        "plt.title(\"Boxplot de la variable Nota\")\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ]
    },
}

